Building HER, I started being more intentional, more specific in what I want myself to look like, my life to look like. Trying my best to be the highest version of myself, and taking care of myself. 

Things that really matter, and are a high priority in my life right now is, making sure I’m hydrated and eating well, taking time to rest, taking time to follow my passions outside of being a mother, praying, asking for help, boundaries, having a 5 min makeup routine, outsourcing, spending time outside for mental breaks. Constantly working on myself and my family 💕 when you are intentional the universe will open up doors for you

#womeninmarketing
We are lucky girls 💕 Allhumdulilah

August 14th-Happy Pakistan Independence Day. There is so much going on in Pakistan and it breaks my heart, praying that things get better. 🇵🇰 Sharing one of my favorite quotes from Quaid e Azam the founder of Pakistan, who had a vision for Pakistan, a true leader.

I read this somewhere and it had me 🥹 Motherhood comes with so many layers. Caught up knee deep in diapers and tantrums. You don’t have as much freedom as you used too, you have FOMO more. Raising little humans is a processsss and you will lose your “pink” along the way, but that okay because it will come back, better and stronger than before 💕 keep going mama

You need to fill your cup mama!! It’s hard but make that time for yourself, take those small steps,make those small changes to better your health. I’m thankful for a partner who fully supports me and understands the importance of self care. We both work as a team and make sure we both are taken care of so we can take be our best selves for our kids….sooo hard right with all 3 still so little but we try our best and take it a day a hour at a time

Marriage….a commitment for a lifetime, that requires constant work and dedication. But, it’s worth it, when you know you found your person. May Allah always guide us. I can’t believe it’s been 11 years!! We were babiessssss and now…loook at us, raising 3 daughters and building the life we dreamt of. May Allah bless everyone with a righteous spouse. Allhumdulilah 💕

I recently made the decision to resign from my 9-5 job in marketing. I absolutely loved the position, but it was getting hard to manage, I have 3 kids 6 and under (Allhumdulilah) and they require a lot of attention. So right now I’m taking a pause and making a shift entering a new era, re discovering myself, and just enjoying all the little moments life has to offer ✨

I’m def a srunchy mom, I’m all about unmedicated childbirth but also have no problem feeding my child formula. How you raise your family is your decisions, there is no one right way. You have to do what works best for you and your family. We all have different backgrounds and beliefs.
Dream big ✨
We have 3 pairs of eyes watching us, trying our best to show up as positive role models for them 💕

The Sea Glass Carousel located at the Battery in Manhattan, New York is such a magical experience. It’s an aquarium themed carousel with light, music, and movement. 
Tickets are $6 per person

We visited Lahore Restaurant in New Jersey. An authentic Pakistani restaurant 🇵🇰

I loved the art work and decor. 
We had the pani puri, samosa chaat, chicken nuggets and fries, charsi Karahi, chicken tikka boti, kulfi, and the Falooda.

We absolutely loved DreamWorks indoor water park!!! It was very well managed, clean! It’s located at the @americandream mall (love that I can also get my shopping done) 

🌊A variety of water slides for both kids and adults, a lazy river, and a wave pool

🌴 Fully relax in an 81°F tropical climate all year round

📏 All rides have posted age and height requirements included

Such a fun time for the whole family, highly recommend!!!

Located in American Dream NJ

I used to always be so stressed about cleaning, just for it to get messy again a few minutes later. I have been trying to be more minimal, and doing quick tidy ups, having the kids put their toys back, and just spending my time trying to be more present and playing with them.
Trying our best to give them the best childhood ✨ also I can’t believe it September already!

I hear this all the time!! Don’t hold the baby too much, you will spoil them! You carried a baby for 9 months, they need time to transition into this world, all they have ever known is you. You can’t spoil a baby that is 6 months and under. 

When you respond quickly to your baby, you're building his sense of self-worth. You're also establishing a foundation of trust that can last for years to come.

I loved baby wearing during the fourth trimester and holding them as much as possible, everything else can wait 💕
NYFW Day One. This def is my favorite time of year in NYC! Each time I attend I feel so inspired and also proud of my journey, it is such a privilege to attend.
It’s important to block out the noise 💕 No one knows your situation better than you do.

This quote is from the movie “Look Both Ways”, it’s about a college graduate who finds out she is pregnant. The movie shows her life in two parallel realities. This movie had me in tears!!!! Being a mom is amazing, no doubt, but it also a lot, it’s hard. It’s a complete life change, everything as we once knew it, changes. We change, how we view the world changes, rediscovering ourselves….it’s a lottttttt. Struggling with self identity and so much more, but I’m here to say that’s it’s normal and it’s okay 💕
Shine Bright Baby!!! ✨✨✨✨ NYFW Day ✌🏽
Behind the scenes 😂 #nyfw

Had some delicious halal Indian food at @aromaindiannyc located in Queens NY. 

We got the mango lassi, pani puri, gobi manchurian, chilli paneer chaat, bamboo biryani, butter chicken, onion kulcha, grilled platter. 

For dessert we got gulab jamun cheesecake, and the ras malai tres leche. 
This is the perfect place to have lunch with the family, also how beautiful is the wall art! 

Thank you for having us @aromaindiannyc

Saw this quote on @shittymommymoments I have accepted the fact that I can’t, I can’t do it all, and that is okay. My house is hardly ever clean, laundry hardly gets folded, and my do list is never ending, and it’s okay. 

There are def moments where I am losing myself in motherhood, but I know there is light at the end of the tunnel.

Wholesome moments like these 💕 my father in law is visiting us, the girls have been over the moon, they love spending time with him, and I love watching them bond. This is what matters to me, for my children to have positive male role models in their lives

With heavy heart of sadness and rage!!! The fact that is happening and showing us whose lives matter and whose don’t. May Allah help our ummah

We celebrated Hania’s second birthday, I couldn’t help but think about the mothers of Gaza who have watched their children suffer for over half a century and now this genocide 😞 holding my babies extra tight and praying 💕
Living life seems like a crime. My heart, breaks, cries for the parents, I wish I could take all the pain away. I cant even look that the videos imagine the ones having to go through it.
We will never forget, how barbaric, how cruel, how unfair!
My heart, I just can’t anymore 😞
